  "text": "In Section 4, we present an other model of gas, that we qualify to be of type 2 (this is not a gas model with nearest neighbor exclusion). The density of this gas model is related to the GF of DA counted according to the area and perimeter (Theorem 4.3). This construction explained once again at the level of object on any agreeable graph a relation used by Bousquet-Mélou [CITATION_1] in a formal way on the square lattice. Even if we haven't find any deep application to this construction, we think that it provides an interesting generic approach to the computation of the GF of DA according to the area and perimeter, and it should lead to new results in the future.",
